{"title_page": "1999 St. George Illawarra Dragons season", "text_new": "{{Infobox rugby league team season|CEO=|CEO_title=CEO|assistant_coach=|avg_attendance=13,259|captain=[[Paul McGregor (rugby league)|Paul McGregor]]|captain2=|coach=[[David Waite]]|cup=|cup_result=|high_attendance=19,181 {{small|(vs. Newcastle, round 24)}}|league=NRL|league_champions=|league_draws=0|league_losses=10|league_rank=6th|league_wins=18|list=|next_season=[[2000 St. George Illawarra Dragons season|2000]]|playoff_result=Runners-Up|points_against=472|points_for=692|prev_season=|stadium=[[Jubilee Oval]],\n[[Wollongong Showground]]|top_goals=[[Wayne Bartrim]] (71)|top_points=[[Wayne Bartrim]] (162)|top_tries=[[Nathan Blacklock]] (24)|year=1999}}The '''1999 St. George Illawarra Dragons season''' was the first in the [[St. George Illawarra Dragons|joint venture club]]'s history. The Dragons competed in the [[National Rugby League|NRL]]'s [[1999 NRL season|1999 premiership season.]] The team finished sixth in the regular season, before making and losing the [[1999 NRL Grand Final|grand final]] against the [[Melbourne Storm]] in front of a record-breaking crowd, with 107,999 people in attendance at the new [[Stadium Australia]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nrl.com/news/2019/09/26/party-like-its-1999-how-storm-upset-dragons-to-kick-off-purple-reign/|title=Party like it's 1999: How Storm upset Dragons to kick off purple reign|date=2019-09-28|website=National Rugby League|language=en|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n\n== Squad Gains and Losses ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:700px;\"\n!{{increase}} or {{decrease}}\n!Player\n!1998 Club\n!1999 Club\n|-\n|{{increase}}\n|{{sortname|Warren|Carney}}\n|N/A\n| rowspan=\"25\" |{{Leagueicon|St. George Illawarra}} [[St. George Illawarra Dragons]]\n|-\n|{{increase}}\n|{{sortname|Trent|Barrett}}\n| rowspan=\"12\" |{{Leagueicon|Illawarra}} [[Illawarra Steelers]]\n|-\n|{{increase}}\n|{{sortname|Craig|Fitzgibbon}}\n|-\n|{{increase}}\n|{{sortnam